# Sage system (global install)

When the user invokes `/sage-*` or asks for Sage SDLC work:

1. New project with no `./runs/` or `.sage-project.json`? Suggest `/sage-init` first.
2. Read the root contract: `./Agents.md` at workspace root if present, else `$HOME/.sage/Agents.md`.
3. Load the matching skill from `$HOME/.sage/skills/` (also linked in `~/.cursor/skills/sage-*`).
4. Write run artifacts under `./runs/<run-id>/` in the current workspace.
5. Role files live in `$HOME/.sage/agents/`. Workflow profiles: `$HOME/.sage/workflows/profiles.md`.

Never skip plan, build, qa, or release except via `manifest.skipped_phases`.
